description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are offering an exciting opportunity for a suitably qualified professional to work as a Band 6 Mental Health Practitioner within the Early Intervention in Psychosis team based at Westcroft.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful applicants will have a working knowledge of people with Psychosis and an enthusiasm to work with a challenging but worthwhile group of service users who, with the correct intervention, can go on to live full and meaningful lives. Much emphasis is placed on the individual service users pathway to Recovery and wellness. Ideally the applicant will have experience /knowledge of first episode psychosis. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful applicant would have access to further training and development and work with a wide range of professionals and other services&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;You must be enthusiastic, patient-centred and have a flexible approach to work. Ability to work effectively independently and within a multi-disciplinary team &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The working hours are Monday to Friday 09.00-17.00 (excluding Bank Holidays)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Car owner/driver essential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We welcome applications from suitably experienced mental health nurses, social workers and occupational therapists.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameCaroline DaviesJob titleTeam ManagerEmail addresscaroline.davies24@nhs.netTelephone number01908 725576Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
